race.comment: ZOUBABY (13) missed the jump but really dug deep in the final stages to record an impressive win in a Class 3 over this course and distance a fortnight ago. Takes on a better race today but drops 3kgs and the hot tempo will suit her racing pattern. Big chance to get the job done again. TALTARNI FIELDS (3) led under pressure and couldn't finish the race off over 1200m here last start. Very effective at this slightly shorter trip. Rarely puts in a bad one so in this suitable race expect him to bounce back to form. FLEETWOOD (1) appreciated the drop in grade when an eye-catching third over 1000m at Eagle Farm most recently. The winner of four from eight at this distance. Major player with the help of the inside draw. HEARTS ARE BETTER (12) resumes. Led all the way to defeat ZOUBABY when fresh from a spell last prep. Honest mare who is a live chance with the light weight. ABOUT TO EXPLODE (4) might find this a bit sharp but he should be powering home at his first run back.
